A recent series of outbreaks in Europe reflects an increasing incidence of listeriosis in the region. In the following graph, I've contrasted disease rates per 100 000 in the European Union with those of the United States [1,2] (graph link: https://www.gideononline.com/2018/03/25/listeriosis-in-the-european-union/).

References:
1. Berger S. Listeriosis: Global Status, 2018: 128 pages, 108 graphs, 1,203 references. Gideon e-books, https://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/listeriosis-global-status/.
2. Gideon e-Gideon multi-graph tool, https://www.gideononline.com/cases/multi-graphs/.

